thority of law and the dictates of conscience in antebellum America's court of public opinion, Caleb Smith offers a new poetics of justice which assesses the nonrational influence that these printed confessions, trial reports, and martyr narratives exerted on their first audiences. Smith shows how writers portrayed struggles for justice as clashes between human law and higher authority, giving voice to a moral protest that transformed American literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aAmerican literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aLaw and literaturezUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSocial justice in literature. 4aHISTORY / United States / 19th Century. 4aHISTORY / United States / Revolutionary Period (1775-1800). 4aLAW / Legal History. 4aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE LITERATURE 2013z978311031726808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2013z9783110317251oZDB-23-DLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014z978311037488908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package 2013z978311037490208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045951708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066256640uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.9780674075849423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674075849.jpg  a978-3-11-031726-8  E-BOOK PACKAGE LITERATURE 2013b2013  a